textAfterTable: 23 Songs Biography Born: October 26, 1913 in New York, NY Genre: Jazz Years Active: '30s, '40s, '50s, '60s, '70s, '80s, '90s Charlie Barnet was unusual in several ways. One of the few jazzmen to be born a millionaire, Barnet was a bit of a playboy throughout his life, ending up with a countless number of ex-wives and anecdotes. He was one of the few white big band leaders of the swing era to openly embrace the music of Duke Ellington (he also greatly admired Count Basie).
